# Reference manifest consumed by `op run --env-file=` for MCP-enabled launches.
# Contains op:// URIs, NEVER secret values. Safe to commit, safe to read.
#
# Usage:
#   op run --account my.1password.com --env-file=$HOME/.config/mcp/common.env -- <tool>
#
# The launched subprocess inherits resolved env vars. Each auth-backed baseline
# MCP server wrapper (mcp-github-server, mcp-brave-search-server,
# mcp-firecrawl-server, mcp-runpod-server, mcp-cloudflare-server) checks its env
# var first and only calls `op read` itself when the var is missing — so
# wrappers still work on bare launches, and `op run` just skips the
# per-subprocess op-read overhead.
#
# See docs/mcp-config.md for the framework and docs/github-mcp.md for the
# GitHub-specific integration.

GITHUB_PAT=op://Dev/github-mcp/token
BRAVE_API_KEY=op://Dev/brave-search/api-key
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=op://Dev/firecrawl/api-key
RUNPOD_API_KEY=op://Dev/runpod-api/api-key
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=op://Dev/cloudflare-mcp-jefahnierocks/token
